to the editor re gale norton rouses congress editorial some editions june 21 you say secretary norton renounced her indisputable authority to recommend to congress lands for wilderness protection the authority you refer to comes from section 603 of the federal land policy and management act of 1976 that authority expired in 1991 you overlook secretary norton 's public commitment to continue to inventory and protect areas with wilderness characteristics secretary norton has also set up a careful process to resolve decades old disputes regarding roads in the west you dismiss this effort labeling it a retreat from responsibility in an agreement with utah secretary norton established procedures through which the state can present documents showing the presence of long maintained roads where proper documentation exists the interior department will recognize these roads the process does not apply to parks refuges or wilderness areas p lynn scarlett assistant secretary policy management and budget department of interior washington june 27 2003

